## Step 1 — Fill in the canonical docs

Before writing any code, update these two files with your actual decisions:

**`docs/CANONICAL_ARCHITECTURE.md`**
Document your stack choices and rationale. Your agents will read this
before generating any code. Vague architecture docs produce vague code.

**`docs/CANONICAL_PATTERNS.md`**
Document the exact coding patterns your project follows. Include examples.
Agents copy patterns — give them good ones to copy.

## Step 2 — Understand your agent conventions

**`AGENTS.md`** is the mandatory entry point for every AI agent working
on this project. It tells agents what to read, what commands to use,
and what rules to follow. Read it now so you understand what your
agents will see.

{{#hasSkills}}
